SGX S&P CNX Nifty Index futures for
March delivery rose 36 points, or 0.7 percent, to 5,515 at 9:06
a.m. in  Singapore .  The futures, derived from the 50 stocks on the underlying
S&P CNX Nifty Index on the National Stock Exchange of India Ltd.,
yesterday dropped 0.9 percent to 5,479 in Singapore, and
retreated 1 percent to 5,466.65 in Mumbai.  To contact the reporter on this story:
